<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2872] ThreadManager deadlock for task expiration</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2872</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a TNonblockingServer running with 1 worker thread and 10 IO thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If there was a big task that just finished, all pending tasks might be expired. In such case, all IO threads are waiting for maxMonitor_, but the worker won&apos;t notify. It will remove all the tasks(all of them are expired) first. And then the notify code won&apos;t be executed because tasks are empty. Deadlock occurs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch move the if-notify statement out so it will notify even if all tasks are removed for expiration.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
